by Gralov » Sat Jan 29, 2022 3:51 am

Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire wrote:The Catgirl Republic has finished constructing the Mow'lasa Line, a defensive line of artillery, walls, bunkers, tunnels, and fortifications to defend the surrounding borders of the Republic. This'll hopefully be helpful in deterring a ground invasion by surrounding Martian factions should an event like that arise.

But the fears of war were true. Images through satellites orbiting Mars and other reconnaissance technology showed that the two factions on Mars, the Ra'ki—dwarf size creatures with orange skin and a humanoid body of orange scales like a lizard—and the Nal'xiso—fifteen-foot tall creatures with eight thin legs (like an arachnid) that hold their round circular body and four arms, and they have light amounts of fur and hair on their body and their head is hunchbacked from the front of their body—were moving ground troops close to the Catgirl borders in the tens of thousands. Ra'ki military spaceships were spotted intimidating exiting Catgirl merchant vessels from Titan and Mars which continued to build up tensions amongst the nations.

M'yri'ah now a top diplomat and explorer of the Catgirl Republic was sent to the Ra'ki capital for peace negotiations but things immediately went downhill as the Ra'ki began citing their religious texts of the Catgirls as being false "abominations" that were mistakenly created by the Martians. And that they should be destroyed to remove them from existing at all. M'yri'ah is then forced out of the city of Ra'ki and disappointedly realizes that war is in the mist.

Nal'xiso spaceships start harassing Catgirl vessels in the asteroid belt, leading to a skirmish between some of the vessels wishing to defend themselves and the Nal'xiso ships worried the Catgirls are threatening their asteroid mining bases. This becomes the last straw and immediately the Nal'xiso and Ra'ki declare war and start offensives. The two Martian factions continue to attempt to get other factions involved in the conflict but for now, it remains them vs the Catgirls.

Fighting rages hard as the Catgirls not only fight for their independence but also their right to exist. The Mow'lasa Line holds itself quite well as the Catgirls utilizing the southern Martian highlands to bombard and send loads of highly explosive artillery shells to suppress the offensive Martian soldiers. The Ra'ki find themselves forced undercover and instead focus on a policy of tunneling to avoid the Catgirl defenses. Nal'xiso military forces focus themselves on fighting the Catgirls in the air and also in space, with major dogfights fought within the asteroid belt utilizing light fighter spaceships to weave through the belt for sortie missions.

Things remain in a stalemate so far but the Catgirls plan a major counteroffensive to drive back the two Martian factions in order to dissuade the other Martian factions from joining the war, making things easier for the Republic.



The earth unites to exterminate catgirls and proceed to go further outer space to hunt the last remnants of their republic.
